l tokenized_dataset\n","gc.collect()\n","\n","print(f\"    Train samples: {len(train_dataset):,}\")\n","print(f\"    Eval samples:  {len(eval_dataset):,}\")\n","if len(train_dataset) > 0:\n","    sample_len = len(train_dataset[0][\"input_ids\"])\n","    print(f\"   First sample length: {sample_len} tokens\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"fb22994f","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004858,"end_time":"2026-04-23T16:28:47.64294+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T16:28:47.638082+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Step 5: Configure the Trainer\n","\n","The HuggingFace `Trainer` is configured with the following key settings:\n","\n","- **Completion-only loss (TRL):** The loss is computed only on the assistant's response, not the prompt. This is achieved by masking all tokens before the `<|im_start|>assistant` token.\n","- **Effective batch size of 8:** Achieved via 1 sample per device with 8 gradient accumulation steps, keeping system RAM usage within the 16 GB Kaggle limit.\n","- **BFloat16 precision:** Matches the model's native dtype. No additional quantization is applied during training.\n","- **Paged AdamW 8-bit optimizer:** Offloads optimizer states to CPU pages, significantly reducing VRAM compared to a standard Adam optimizer.\n","- **Cosine learning rate schedule:** Learning rate decays smoothly from the peak to near zero over the full epoch.\n","- **Evaluation every 250 steps:** Both `per_device_eval_batch_size` and `eval_accumulation_steps` are set to 1 to prevent out-of-memory errors at eval time, as HuggingFace defaults these to higher values."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":12,"id":"57891fcc","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T16:28:47.653287Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T16:28:47.653151Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T16:28:54.171472Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T16:28:54.171122Z"},"papermill":{"duration":6.524342,"end_time":"2026-04-23T16:28:54.172108+00:00","exception":f