okenizer.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n","\n","# Report disk usage\n","import shutil\n","adapter_size = sum(\n","    os.path.getsize(os.path.join(dp, f))\n","    for dp, _, fns in os.walk(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n","    for f in fns\n",") / (1024 * 1024)\n","disk_usage = shutil.disk_usage(\"/kaggle/working\")\n","print(f\"\\n LoRA adapter saved to: {ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"   Adapter size: {adapter_size:.1f} MB\")\n","print(f\"   Disk remaining: {disk_usage.free / (1024**3):.1f} GB\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b95547c7","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.00542,"end_time":"2026-04-23T18:15:13.999482+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T18:15:13.994062+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Step 9: Inference Test\n","\n","A quick inference test is run to verify the model has learned the required output format. A math problem is passed to the model with the reasoning system prompt active. The generated output is checked for:\n","\n","- A closing `</think>` tag -- confirms the model learned to close its chain-of-thought block.\n","- A `\\\\boxed{}` final answer -- confirms the model learned to produce a structured answer.\n","\n","If both are present, Phase 1 is considered successful."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":16,"id":"f5b3758f","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T18:15:14.01109Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T18:15:14.010911Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.752628Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.752268Z"},"papermill":{"duration":227.750413,"end_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.755367+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T18:15:14.004954+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["WARNING:transformers_modules._1.modeling_nemotron_h:NemotronH requires an initialized `NemotronHHybridDynamicCache` to return a cache. None was provided, so no cache will be returned.\n"]},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n"," RUNNING INFERENCE TEST...\n","\n","--- FULL OUTPUT ---\n","<|im_start|>system\n","detailed thinking on<|im_end|>\n","<|im_start|>user\n","If f(x) = x^2 + 3x - 4, find all values of x where f(x) = 0. Show full working.<|im_end|>\n","<|im_start|>assistant\n","<think>\n","We need to solve the quadratic equation \\(f(x) = x^2 + 3x - 4 = 0\\).\n","**Step 1: Identify coefficients**\n","The equation is in standard form \\(ax^2 + bx + c = 0\\):\n","- \\(a = 1\\)\n","- \\(b = 3\\)\n","- \\(c = -4\\)\n","\n","**Step 2: Calculate the discriminant (\\(D\\))**\n","\\(D = b^2 - 4ac\\)\n","\\(D = 3^2 - 4(1)(-4)\\)\n","\\(D = 9 + 16 = 25\\)\n","\n","**Step 3: Find square roots of the discriminant**\n","\\(\\sqrt{25} = 5\\)\n","\n","**Step 4: Apply the quadratic formula**\n","\\[x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{D}}{2a}\\]\n","Substituting our values:\n","\\[x = \\frac{-3 \\pm 5}{2 \\times 1}\\]\n","\n","**Step 5: Solve for both possibilities**\n","- With the plus sign: \\(x = \\frac{-3 + 5}{2} = \\frac{2}{2} = 1\\)\n","- With the minus sign: \\(x = \\frac{-3 - 5}{2} = \\frac{-8}{2} = -4\\)\n","\n","Thus, the solutions are \\(x = 1\\) and \\(x = -4\\).\n","\n","**Verification by factoring:**\n","Rewrite the original equation as a product equal to zero.\n","\\(x^2 + 3x - 4 = (x - 1)(x + 4) = 0\\)\n","Setting each factor to zero gives the same results:\n","- \\(x - 1 = 0 \\implies x = 1\\)\n","- \\(x + 4 = 0 \\implies x = -4\\)\n","\n","Both methods confirm the solutions.\n","</think>\n","\\boxed{1,\\ -4}<|im_end|>\n","-------------------\n","\n","--- GENERATED PORTION ONLY ---\n","We need to solve the quadratic equation \\(f(x) = x^2 + 3x - 4 = 0\\).\n","**Step 1: Identify coefficients**\n","The equation is in standard form \\(ax^2 + bx + c = 0\\):\n","- \\(a = 1\\)\n","- \\(b = 3\\)\n","- \\(c = -4\\)\n","\n","**Step 2: Calculate the discriminant (\\(D\\))**\n","\\(D = b^2 - 4ac\\)\n","\\(D = 3^2 - 4(1)(-4)\\)\n","\\(D = 9 + 16 = 25\\)\n","\n","**Step 3: Find square roots of the discriminant**\n","\\(\\sqrt{25} = 5\\)\n","\n","**Step 4: Apply the quadratic formula**\n","\\[x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{D}}{2a}\\]\n","Substituting our values:\n","\\[x = \\frac{-3 \\pm 5}{2 \\times 1}\\]\n","\n","**Step 5: Solve for both possibilities**\n","- With the plus sign: \\(x = \\frac{-3 + 5}{2} = \\frac{2}{2} = 1\\)\n","- With the minus sign: \\(x = \\frac{-3 - 5}{2} = \\frac{-8}{2} = -4\\)\n","\n","Thus, the solutions are \\(x = 1\\) and \\(x = -4\\).\n","\n","**Verification by factoring:**\n","Rewrite the original equation as a product equal to zero.\n","\\(x^2 + 3x - 4 = (x - 1)(x + 4) = 0\\)\n","Setting each factor to zero gives the same results:\n","- \\(x - 1 = 0 \\implies x = 1\\)\n","- \\(x + 4 = 0 \\implies x = -4\\)\n","\n","Both methods confirm the solutions.\n","</think>\n","\\boxed{1,\\ -4}<|im_end|>\n","-------------------\n","\n"," PHASE 1 MISSION SUCCESS — <think>...</think> + \\boxed{} confirmed.\n","PHASE 1 COMPLETE (supervised Fine tuning for Nemotron completed).\n"]}],"source":["print(\"\\n RUNNING INFERENCE TEST...\\n\")\n","\n","model.eval()\n","\n","# Build prompt directly — model generates everything after <think>\n","test_prompt = (\n","    \"<|im_start|>system\\n\"\n","    \"detailed thinking on<|im_end|>\\n\"\n","    \"<|im_start|>user\\n\"\n","    \"If f(x) = x^2 + 3x - 4, find all values of x where f(x) = 0. Show full working.<|im_end|>\\n\"\n","    \"<|im_start|>assistant\\n\"\n","    \"<think>\\n\"\n",")\n","\n","inputs = tokenizer(test_prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(\"cuda\")\n","prompt_len = inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n","\n","with torch.inference_mode():\n","    outputs = model.generate(\n","        **inputs,\n","        max_new_tokens  = 1024,\n","        temperature     = 0.6,\n","        top_p           = 0.95,\n","        do_sample       = True,\n","        eos_token_id    = tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n","        repetition_penalty = 1.1\n","    )\n","\n","# Decode full output and generated-only portion separately\n","full_response = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=False)\n","generated_text = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0][prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=False)\n","\n","print(\"--- FULL OUTPUT ---\")\n","print(full_response)\n","print(\"-------------------\")\n","print(\"\\n--- GENERATED PORTION ONLY ---\")\n","print(generated_text)\n","print(\"-------------------\")\n","\n","# Validate format on generated text only (not the injected prompt)\n","has_think_close = \"</think>\" in generated_text\n","has_boxed = \"\\\\boxed{\" in generated_text\n","\n","if has_think_close and has_boxed:\n","    print(\"\\n PHASE 1 MISSION SUCCESS — <think>...</think> + \\\\boxed{} confirmed.\")\n","elif has_think_close:\n","    print(\"\\n  </think> found but \\\\boxed{} missing in output.\")\n","elif has_boxed:\n","    print(\"\\n  \\\\boxed{} found but </think> closure missing — format partially learned.\")\n","else:\n","    print(\"\\n WARNING — Neither </think> nor \\\\boxed{} detected. More training may be needed.\")\n","\n","# Final cleanup\n","del inputs, outputs\n","gc.collect()\n","torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n","\n","print(\"PHASE 1 COMPLETE (supervised Fine tuning for Nemotron completed).\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"a698a3ed","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005538,"end_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.76648+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.760942+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Section 2: GRPO Training\n","\n","**GRPO (Group Relative Policy Optimization)** is a reinforcement-learning-from-reward-signals\n","algorithm that teaches the model to *prefer* correct, well-formatted answers by comparing\n","multiple sampled completions against each other — without a separate value/critic network.\n","\n","### How it works (plain-language)\n","1. For each question the model samples a **group** of G candidate completions.\n","2. A set of **reward functions** scores every candidate (format + answer correctness).\n","3. Candidates are ranked inside the group. The model is nudged toward high-reward completions\n","   and away from low-reward ones via a clipped surrogate loss (same spirit as PPO).\n","4. A **KL-divergence** penalty keeps the policy from drifting too far from the SFT init.\n","\n","### Pipeline\n","\n","| Step | What happens |\n","|------|--------------|\n","| 1 | Reload SFT adapter + load GRPO dataset |\n","| 2 | Define reward functions (format + correctness) |\n","| 3 | Configure `GRPOTrainer` + `GRPOConfig` |\n","| 4 | VRAM safety check |\n","| 5 | Run GRPO training |\n","| 6 | Save updated LoRA adapter |"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"6826fdaf","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005504,"end_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.777524+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.77202+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Step 1: Reload the SFT Adapter and Load the GRPO Dataset\n","\n","The base model is already in memory from Section 1. We reload the SFT adapter so GRPO\n","starts from the fine-tuned checkpoint — not from the raw base model.\n","\n","The GRPO dataset (`FINAL_DATA_GRPO.csv`) must contain **`question`** and **`answer`** columns.\n","The `answer` column must include a `\\\\boxed{}` ground-truth so the correctness reward can fire."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":17,"id":"4a7d18fb","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.789284Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.789153Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.791409Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.791191Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.008826,"end_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.79189+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-23T18:19:01.783064+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["# import gc\n","# import torch\n","# import os\n","# from datasets import load_dataset\n","# from peft import PeftModel\n","# from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n","# import datasets\n","